  <fr:p>To define the bottom element of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we choose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha {\mathopen {}\left (\bot , \lambda \_.\star \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we must check that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha {\mathopen {}\left (\bot , \lambda \_.\star \right )\mathclose {}}\sqsubseteq  n]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {L}]]></fr:tex> is a Kock–Zöberlein monad and thus we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \dashv \eta _{A}]]></fr:tex>, it is equivalent to observe that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\bot , \lambda \_.\star \right )\mathclose {}}\sqsubseteq  \eta _{A}n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
